<TITLE> Pakistan urges India not to play politics </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW DELHI, Nov 28(bdnews24.com/Reuters) -Pakistan Foreign Minister Shah Mehmood Qureshi said on Friday that India and Pakistan should join hands to defeat a common enemy, and urged New Delhi not to play politics over the attacks in Mumbai. "Do not bring politics into this issue. This is a collective issue. We are facing a common enemy and we should join hands to defeat the enemy," the foreign minister told reporters in Ajmer.
